The assay for scavenging hydroxyl radicals (OH∙-) was conducted by Kunchandy and Rao49. The absorbance of the plant extracts was measured at A532 nm and compared to that of a blank consisting of buffer and deoxyribose. One milliliter of reaction mixture containing 500 µl of previously prepared extracts of different concentrations (3–1000 µg/ml) and 100 µl of each of 2-deoxy-D-ribose (28 mM), EDTA (1.04 mM), FeCl3 (0.2 mM) or ascorbic acid (1.0 mM) was incubated at 37 °C for 1 h. The inhibition of deoxyribose was calculated via the following formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
